# Sync exclusions for the nodejs dependency.
#
# Strategy: Part A (landed 2026-05-15) narrowed vcbuild.bat so the
# narrow build skips node.exe / libnode / cctest / embedtest /
# openssl-cli / fuzz_* / nop / overlapped-checker. Part B (this
# file) drops on-disk content those targets needed but the v8jsi
# closure does not — non-Windows OpenSSL arches, V8 test corpus,
# Node.js JS test corpus, doc/, pure-JS deps, etc.
#
# A future libnode.dll build may need to un-prune some of these:
# - ICU if libnode ships with Intl.
# - Other libnode-graph deps stay pruned because libnode.dll
#   doesn't need their tests / docs / openssl-cli / fuzz corpora.

# ── CI/CD configurations (already excluded; kept for visibility) ────
.configurations/
.devcontainer/
.github/

# ── Documentation & benchmark trees (no build-step consumer) ────────
/doc/
/benchmark/
/typings/
/android-patches/

# ── JS test corpus — Node.js test runner, not msbuild ───────────────
# Post-Part-A the cctest / embedtest / fuzzers / nop / overlapped-
# checker C++ targets are also skipped. Keeping the 5 subdirs anyway
# because (a) they're < 1 MB combined and (b) configure.py:1553-1554
# calls SearchFiles('test/cctest', ...) unconditionally — keeping
# the dir avoids any risk of configure breakage.
/test/*
!/test/cctest/
!/test/cctest/**
!/test/fuzzers/
!/test/fuzzers/**
!/test/embedding/
!/test/embedding/**
!/test/overlapped-checker/
!/test/overlapped-checker/**
!/test/nop/
!/test/nop/**

# ── Pure-JS package-manager assets — never compiled by msbuild ─────
/deps/npm/
/deps/corepack/

# ── tools/ — drop non-build subtrees ────────────────────────────────
/tools/doc/
/tools/lint-md/
/tools/eslint/
/tools/eslint-rules/
/tools/dep_updaters/
/tools/actions/
/tools/clang-format/
/tools/macos-installer/
/tools/pip/
/tools/zos/

# ── deps/openssl/config/archs/ — keep only Windows MSVC + .gypi stubs ─
# Empirical finding (Part B stage 2): GYP resolves conditional include
# paths in openssl_{,no_,_avx2}asm.gypi at parse time regardless of
# target_arch/OS guards, so every arch's <variant>/openssl{,-cl,-fips}.gypi
# must exist on disk for gyp configure to succeed. The .gypi files are
# tiny (~0.21 MB per arch); the 9-17 MB bulk is the asm / crypto /
# include / providers / engines / apps source trees, none of which the
# Part-A narrow build compiles for non-Windows arches.
#
# Pattern uses last-match-wins ordering: drop the variant content
# universally, re-include .gypi files at variant level, then re-include
# Windows arches in full at the end so they trump the universal drop.
/deps/openssl/config/archs/*
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/asm/
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/asm_avx2/
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/no-asm/
/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/asm/**
/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/asm_avx2/**
/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/no-asm/**
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/asm/*.gypi
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/asm_avx2/*.gypi
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/*/no-asm/*.gypi
# Windows arches kept fully (x86 / x64 / arm64 build compiles them).
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/VC-WIN32/
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/VC-WIN32/**
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/VC-WIN64A/
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/VC-WIN64A/**
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/VC-WIN64-ARM/
!/deps/openssl/config/archs/VC-WIN64-ARM/**

# ── deps/openssl/openssl/ internals — drop test/doc/cli source ─────
# These are referenced only by the openssl-cli and fuzz_* targets
# which Part A excludes from the build.
/deps/openssl/openssl/apps/
/deps/openssl/openssl/fuzz/
/deps/openssl/openssl/doc/
/deps/openssl/openssl/external/
/deps/openssl/openssl/tools/
/deps/openssl/openssl/VMS/
/deps/openssl/openssl/os-dep/

# ── deps/v8/test/ — V8's own test corpus, not built ────────────────
# Exception: test/torque/test-torque.tq is referenced as an input to
# the run_torque codegen step (V8 ships its torque smoke test as part
# of the codegen input set). Keep that one file; drop everything else.
/deps/v8/test/*
!/deps/v8/test/torque/
!/deps/v8/test/torque/test-torque.tq
/deps/v8/samples/
/deps/v8/docs/

# ── deps/v8/tools/ — drop V8 dev/debug JS tooling, not built ────────
# turbolizer (IR visualizer) and clusterfuzz/js_fuzzer (fuzzing harness)
# are developer tools, never compiled into v8jsi.dll. Their npm deps —
# and the root tools/package.json — raise Component Governance CVE alerts
# for code we never ship. The rest of tools/ (torque inputs, testrunner)
# stays.
/deps/v8/tools/turbolizer/
/deps/v8/tools/clusterfuzz/
/deps/v8/tools/package.json
/deps/v8/tools/package-lock.json

# ── deps/v8/third_party/ — drop POSIX-only / unreferenced sub-libs ─
/deps/v8/third_party/valgrind/
/deps/v8/third_party/ittapi/
/deps/v8/third_party/vtune/
/deps/v8/third_party/glibc/
/deps/v8/third_party/colorama/

# ── ICU (we ship --without-intl; reversible if Intl returns) ───────
/deps/icu-small/
/deps/icu-tmp/

# ── deps/uv/ internals — drop POSIX impl, tests, docs, img ─────────
/deps/uv/test/
/deps/uv/docs/
/deps/uv/img/
/deps/uv/src/unix/

# ── deps/zlib/google/test/ — Chromium zip wrapper test corpus ──────
# Node's deps/zlib/google/ (zip.cc, compression_utils, …) is unused by
# our build — no .gyp references it; V8 uses its own zlib copy under
# deps/v8/third_party/zlib. The test/ data is deliberately-malformed
# "evil" zips that trip the supply-chain scanner (Phalanx/Armory).
/deps/zlib/google/test/

# ── deps/cares/ — drop docs & autoconf macros ──────────────────────
/deps/cares/docs/
/deps/cares/m4/

# ── Unused deps with no .gyp targets (verified by grep of *.gyp*) ──
# LIEF: single-executable-app packaging tool. No .gyp reference
#   anywhere in deps/nodejs/; no reference from v8-jsi.
# amaro / undici / acorn / minimatch: pure-JS bundles referenced
#   only from node.gyp's deps_files list (lines 64-66) and
#   config.gypi (lines 489-490) — consumed by node_js2c, which
#   doesn't run in the post-Part-A narrow build.
# NOTE: deps/merve/ stays — it has merve.gyp which node.gypi:230
#   references as a libnode dep. Pruning it would break gyp configure
#   even though merve never compiles in narrow mode.
/deps/LIEF/
/deps/amaro/
/deps/undici/
/deps/acorn/
/deps/minimatch/

# ── Top-level loose files unused by build ───────────────────────────
/CHANGELOG.md
/BUILDING.md
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
/CONTRIBUTING.md
/GOVERNANCE.md
/SECURITY.md
/README.md
/glossary.md
/onboarding.md
/codecov.yml
/.gitpod.yml
/android-configure
/android_configure.py

# ── Files flagged by Microsoft Secure Supply Chain Analysis ─────────
# None of these are read by our build; dropping them clears the SSCA
# findings without touching any consumed Node.js content.
#
# /.npmrc            — Node.js core dev tooling (ignore-scripts=true);
#                      we don't run npm inside deps/nodejs/.
# /tools/msvs/msi/   — Node.js MSI installer build; we don't pack it.
# /deps/openssl/config/Dockerfile — used by upstream OpenSSL maintainers
#                      to regenerate config; never executed by our build.
/.npmrc
/tools/msvs/msi/
/deps/openssl/config/Dockerfile
